General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 46, or 59 thereof, and further excepting G.S. 14-82, 14-145, 14-183, 14-184,
2 14-186, 14-190.9, 14-247, 14-248, or 14-313 thereof, and either of the
3 following conditions is met:
4 a. The offense is committed with the intent to benefit, promote, or further
5 the interests of a criminal gang or for the purposes of increasing a
6 person's own standing or position within a criminal gang.
7 b. The participants in the offense are identified as criminal gang members
8 acting individually or collectively to further any criminal purpose of a
9 criminal gang.collectively.
10 (3) Criminal gang leader or organizer. – Any criminal gang member who acts in
11 any position of management with regard to the criminal gang and who meets
12 two or more at least one of the following criteria:
13 a. Exercises decision-making authority over matters regarding a criminal
14 gang.
15 b. Participates in the direction, planning, organizing, or commission of
16 criminal gang activity.
17 c. Recruits other gang members.
18 d. Receives a larger portion of the proceeds of criminal gang activity.
19 e. Exercises control and authority over other criminal gang members.
20 (4) Criminal gang member. – Any person who meets three two or more of the
21 following criteria:
22 a. The person admits to being a member of a criminal gang.
23 b. The person is identified as a criminal gang member by a reliable
24 source, including a parent or a guardian.
25 c. The person has been previously involved in criminal gang activity.
26 d. The person has adopted symbols, hand signs, or graffiti associated
27 with a criminal gang.
28 e. The person has adopted the display of colors or the style of dress
29 associated with a criminal gang.
30 f. The person is in possession of or linked to a criminal gang by physical
31 evidence, including photographs, ledgers, rosters, written or electronic
32 communications, or membership documents.
33 g. The person has tattoos or markings associated with a criminal gang.
34 h. The person has adopted language or terminology associated with a
35 criminal gang.
36 i. The person appears in any form of social media to promote a criminal
37 gang."
38 SECTION 2.(b) This section becomes effective December 1, 2026, and applies to
39 offenses committed on or after that date.
40 SECTION 3.(a) G.S. 14-50.17 reads as rewritten:
41 "§ 14-50.17. Soliciting; encouraging participation.
42 (a) It is unlawful for any person to cause, encourage, solicit, or coerce a person 16 18
43 years of age or older to participate in criminal gang activity. For purposes of this section, causing,
44 encouraging, soliciting, or coercing a person to participate in criminal gang activity includes
45 communications created or shared online, including through social media platforms, whether the
46 communications are shared publicly or privately.
47 (b) A violation of this section is a Class H Class F felony."
48 SECTION 3.(b) G.S. 14-50.18 reads as rewritten:
49 "§ 14-50.18. Soliciting; encouraging participation; minor.
50 (a) It is unlawful for any person to cause, encourage, solicit, or coerce a person under 16
51 18 years of age to participate in criminal gang activity. For purposes of this section, causing,
